wiki.content: The song was released as a single from Britney Spears' first greatest hits album 'Greatest Hits: My Prerogative.' It is a cover of My Prerogative by Bobby Brown. Brown wrote the song about making decisions in one's life and not caring about other people's judgment. Although the song only appeared in component charts in the United States, Spears' cover surpassed Brown's version worldwide, peaking at the top of the charts in Finland, Ireland, Italy and Norway and reaching the top ten in another fourteen countries. The music video portrays Spears arriving at a Hollywood manor in which a party is taking place. In the end, it is revealed that the party is actually Spears' wedding.
